The paper presents a new approach to robust Gaussian process regression, which is a machine learning technique used for regression and probabilistic modeling. The paper focuses on the development of a new approach to handle outliers in the data, which is a common problem in machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.ST (Statistics). Additionally, the paper also discusses the application of the proposed approach to two measurement systems, which suggests the possibility of the paper belonging to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
